Dr. '''Lawrence R. Hafstad''' (1904<U+2013>1993) was an American [[physicist]] who in 1939 created first [[nuclear fission]] reaction in the [[United States]].
<ref name="NYT">[http://www.nytimes.com/1993/10/22/obituaries/lawrence-r-hafstad-dies-at-89-helped-to-develop-nuclear-power.html New York Times:Lawrence R. Hafstad Dies at 89; Helped to Develop Nuclear Power;By WOLFGANG SAXON;October 22, 1993]</ref>
<ref name="NAP">[http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=4779&page=105 Memorial Tributes: National Academy of Engineering, Volume 7 (1994);LAWRENCE R. HAFSTAD;BY JOHN D. CAPLAN;]</ref>
<ref>[http://www.trumanlibrary.org/hstpaper/hafstad.htm Harry S truman museum;Lawrence R. Hafstad Papers;Dates: 1939-1975 ]</ref>
Hafstad was also notable for his pioneering work on nuclear reactors.<ref name="NYT"/>
Hafstad was elected to the [[National Academy of Engineering]].<ref name="NAP"/>
Hafstad was also vice president and chief of research laboratories of [[General Motors]].<ref name="NYT"/>
